n%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20least%20800%20square%20kilometres%20was%20under%20Ukrainian%20control%20as%20of%20Monday%2C%20according%20to%20an%20AFP%20analysis%20of%20data%20from%20the%20US-based%20Institute%20for%20the%20Study%20of%20War.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EForeign%20ministry%20spokesman%20Georgiy%20Tykhy%20on%20Tuesday%20said%20Kyiv%20was%20not%20interested%20in%20%26quot%3Btaking%20over%26quot%3B%20Russian%20territory%20and%20defended%20Ukraine's%20actions%20as%20%26quot%3Babsolutely%20legitimate%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20sooner%20Russia%20agrees%20to%20restore%20a%20just%20peace...%20the%20sooner%20the%20raids%20by%20the%20Ukrainian%20defences%20forces%20into%20Russia%20will%20stop%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20reporters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUkraine%20meanwhile%20said%20it%20was%20imposing%20movement%20restrictions%20in%20a%2020-kilometre%20zone%20in%20Sumy%20region%20along%20the%20border%20with%20Kursk%20region%20due%20to%20an%20%26quot%3Bincrease%20in%20the%20intensity%20of%20hostilities%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bsabotage%26quot%3B%20activities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia's%20defence%20ministry%20said%20it%20had%20%26quot%3Bfoiled%26quot%3B%20new%20Ukrainian%20attacks%20in%20Kursk%20by%20%26quot%3Benemy%20mobile%20groups%20in%20armoured%20vehicles%20to%20break%20through%20deep%20into%20Russian%20territory%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlexander%20Bortnikov%2C%20head%20of%20Russia's%20FSB%20security%20service%2C%20also%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20Ukraine%20had%20carried%20out%20the%20attack%20%26quot%3Bwith%20the%20support%20of%20the%20collective%20West%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'I%20saw%20a%20lot%20of%20death'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20launching%20its%20invasion%20in%20February%202022%2C%20Russia%20has%20captured%20territory%20in%20southern%20and%20eastern%20Ukraine%20and%20subjected%20Ukrainian%20cities%20to%20missile%20and%20drone%20barrages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUkraine's%20offensive%20was%20the%20biggest%20cross-border%20action%20since%20the%20invasion%20and%20it%20caught%20Russia%20off%20guard.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20didn't%20protect%20the%20border%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Ukrainian%20serviceman%20who%20took%20part%20in%20the%20offensive%20and%20identified%20himself%20as%20Ruzhyk%20told%20AFP%20in%20Sumy%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20only%20had%20anti-personnel%20mines%20scattered%20around%20trees%20at%20the%20side%20of%20the%20road%20and%20a%20few%20mines%20that%20they%20managed%20to%20quickly%20throw%20along%20the%20highways%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%2027-year-old%20squad%20leader%2C%20who%20identified%20himself%20as%20Faraon%2C%20was%20sparing%20but%20direct%20in%20his%20description%20of%20battles%20in%20Kursk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20saw%20a%20lot%20of%20death%20in%20the%20first%20few%20days.%20It%20was%20terrifying%20at%20first%20but%20then%20we%20got%20used%20to%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20have%20been%20many%20deaths%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20repeated%20stood%20next%20to%20a%20forest%20road%20leading%20to%20the%20frontier%2C%20without%20elaborating.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUkrainian%20military%20analyst%20Mykola%20Bielieskov%20told%20AFP%3A%20%26quot%3BRussian%20complacency%20prevailed%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRussia%20assumed%20that%20since%20it%20had%20initiative%20elsewhere%2C%20Ukraine%20wouldn't%20dare%20to%20do%20things%20we've%20seen%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20months%20of%20Russian%20advances%20along%20the%20front.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EISW%20figures%20also%20showed%20that%20Russian%20troops%20had%20captured%201%2C360%20square%20kilometres%20of%20Ukrainian%20territory%20since%20the%20start%20of%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Sow%20discord'%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20has%20vowed%20to%20%26quot%3Bdislodge%26quot%3B%20Ukrainian%20troops.%3C%2F